				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$\mbox{C}/\mbox{cm}^{2}$\end{document} of charge emission but no significant degradation in gain (black, left axis) and count rate (blue, right axis) over the duration of the test (results were similar for the two stacks). The count rate, which is a good proxy for the stack efficiency, was derived as the zeroth integral moment of the pulse height distribution performed between limits and geometry that did not change over the life of the test. Thus the pre-conditioning procedure of 0.1C/cm2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
