The DES and DIS HVPS are similar and yet have important differences. In both cases, the HVPS contains three separate high voltage supplies co-located in the same enclosure. Two of these supplies provide separate and independent static high voltage outputs for the two DxS MCP/anode assemblies, positive (up to +3.6kV\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
