To accomplish measurements at all 32 required energies and 4 azimuth zones with the required temporal resolution of 30 ms (DES) or 150 ms (DIS), the DxS ESA voltage and deflector voltages are stepped rapidly as illustrated in Fig. 26, where nominal maximum and minimum energy target centers are shown (actuals for DES or DIS may be slightly different). In 7.5 ms (DES) or 37.5 ms (DIS), the HVPS ESA stepper output is stepped through a progression of 32 logarithmically spaced voltage steps (say the even steps, 0,2,…,60,62\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
