There is another important effect of the lack of shielding between the MCP high voltage and the ESA. Figure 36 shows representative rays from the SIMION study illustrating the electrostatic focusing properties near the exit of the ESA. The variation in radial spot size is large and minimizes within the DIS E/q\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
